*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: the clinical signs observed in the outbreaks are: diarrhea, ocular-nasal discharge, neurological signs, respiratory signs and high mortality. Other control measures: quarantine on the infected farms, destruction and burial of carcasses, disinfection and depopulation of the infected farms and booster vaccination of the non-infected farms.

Control measures
Measures applied: screening; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory) / Birds / real-time reverse transcriptase/polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 22 May 2014/ Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

